Step 2: Core Concept First (The "How Does It Actually Work" Part)
This is what you wanted to understand. Here's the simple mental model:
User gives you:  https://www.google.com/very/long/url
You give back:   tiny.url/a1B2c3

The magic:
1. Generate a unique integer ID     → 123456
2. Encode that ID in Base62         → "a1B2c3"
3. Store the mapping in DB          → "a1B2c3" : "https://google.com/..."
4. When someone visits tiny.url/a1B2c3
   → look up "a1B2c3" in DB
   → redirect to original URL

